'''Bengt Per Anders Nilsson''' (born 19 March 1990) is a [[Swedish people|Swedish]] professional [[ice hockey]] [[goaltender]], currently playing for [[Lule<U+00E5> HF]] in [[Elitserien]]. He was drafted 62nd overall by the [[New York Islanders]] in the [[2009 NHL Entry Draft]].

==International==
{{MedalTableTop|}}
{{MedalCountry | {{ih|Sweden}} }}
{{MedalSport | Men's [[ice hockey]]}}
{{MedalCompetition|[[IIHF World U20 Championship|World Junior Championships]]}}
{{MedalBronze | [[2010 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships|2010 Saskatoon]] | Ice hockey }}
{{MedalBottom}}

Nilsson represented Sweden at the [[2010 World Junior Ice Hockey Championships]] which were held in [[Saskatchewan]], [[Canada]].  He only played in one game during the tournament, as [[Jacob Markstrom]] was the starter.  Sweden won a bronze medal at the tournament.

